# Plot Average for N=100
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

for i in range(0, 21, 4):
    # deep copy
    dfNewN100 = dfNew.copy()
    dfNewN100 = dfNewN100.iloc[i:i+4, :]
    # average row
    dfNewN100.loc['Average'] = dfNewN100.mean()
    # # sort by Average
    # dfNewN100 = dfNewN100.sort_values(by="Average", axis=1, ascending=False)
    # print(dfNewN100)
    str = dfNewN100.index.tolist()[:-1]
    str = ', '.join(str)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))
    if i == 20:
        str = "all istances"
    
    plot = dfNewN100.loc['Average'].plot(kind='bar', ax=ax, color=[colors[h] for h in dfNewN100.columns], align='edge', width=0.8)
    ax.set_ylabel("Improvement (%)")
    ax.set_xlabel("Operator")
    ax.set_title(f"Average improvement of operators for {str}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
